'''列昂尼德·丹尼洛维奇·库奇马'''（{{lang-uk|Леоні́д Дани́лович Ку́чма}}，{{bd|1938年|8月9日|||catIdx=K}}），[[乌克兰|乌克兰]]政治人物。第二任[[乌克兰总统|乌克兰总统]]。

== 生平 ==
列昂尼德·库奇马1938年8月9日生于[[切尔尼戈夫州|切尔尼戈夫州]]北诺夫哥罗德区恰基诺村。1960年，毕业于第聂伯罗彼得罗夫斯克大学。1991年，成为乌克兰工程科学院院士。

1992年10月至1993年9月間出任[[乌克兰总理|乌克兰总理]]。1994年7月在[[1994年乌克兰总统选举|第二轮选举]]中以52.3%的得票率当选总统。1999年11月再次在[[1999年乌克兰总统选举|第二轮选举]]中以57.7%的得票率当选連任总统。2005年1月，卸任总统。

2011年，列昂尼德·库奇马被控与2000年的记者[[格奥尔基·贡加泽|格奥尔基·贡加泽]]被害案有关。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ftchinese.com/story/001037737/?print=y |title=乌克兰前总统被控涉嫌记者谋杀案 |accessdate=2011-03-27 |archive-date=2018-07-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180727181239/http://www.ftchinese.com/story/001037737/?print=y |dead-url=no }}</ref>

庫奇馬也是迄今唯一連任成功的烏克蘭總統。

2014年6月21日，庫奇馬代表烏克蘭政府與[[頓涅茨克人民共和國|頓涅茨克]]、[[盧甘斯克人民共和國|盧甘斯克]]的武裝分離主義叛軍進行談判，討論總統[[彼得·波羅申科|彼得·波羅申科]]的和平計劃<ref>{{cite web|title=NSDC Says Medvedchuk not Representing Ukraine at Peace Plan Talks|url=http://www.ukrinform.net/rubric-politics/1677760-nsdc_says_medvedchuk_not_representing_ukraine_at_peace_plan_talks_323058.html|website=Ukrinform|date=24 June 2014|access-date=5 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160530025259/http://www.ukrinform.net/rubric-politics/1677760-nsdc_says_medvedchuk_not_representing_ukraine_at_peace_plan_talks_323058.html|archive-date=30 May 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="washingtonpost.com">{{cite news|last1=Birnbaum|first1=Michael|title=Separatists in Ukraine Agree to Honor Cease-fire|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/separatists-in-ukraine-agree-to-honor-cease-fire/2014/06/23/40582a78-fb07-11e3-b1f4-8e77c632c07b_story.html|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=23 June 2014|accessdate=2022-05-02|archive-date=2021-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210303194417/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/separatists-in-ukraine-agree-to-honor-cease-fire/2014/06/23/40582a78-fb07-11e3-b1f4-8e77c632c07b_story.html}}</ref>，參與[[新明斯克協議|新明斯克協議]]的簽訂。該計劃確保了停火的實施；歐洲領導人對此反應普遍積極<ref>{{Cite news|title = Ukraine crisis: Leaders agree peace roadmap – BBC News|work = BBC News|date = 12 February 2015|url = https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-31435812|access-date = 2016-01-13|language = en-GB|archive-date = 2021-01-04|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210104031648/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-31435812}}</ref>。2015年3月，他發表講話，批評俄羅斯支持的叛軍圖謀奪取[[傑巴利采韋|傑巴利采韋]]。同年9月，他被任命為{{Link-en|烏克蘭三方聯絡組|Trilateral Contact Group on Ukraine}}的烏克蘭代表，在[[白俄羅斯|白俄羅斯]][[明斯克|明斯克]]舉行會議，討論結束[[頓巴斯戰爭|頓巴斯的衝突]]。2017年3月，他要求俄羅斯聯邦廢除其關於承認在分離主義控制地區簽發的護照的法令<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.kyivpost.com/ukraine-politics/kyiv-insists-cancellation-separatists-ids-recognition-russia.html|title=Kyiv insists on cancellation of separatists IDs recognition by Russia {{!}} KyivPost|date=2017-03-15|work=KyivPost|access-date=2017-05-04|language=en-US|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111235555/https://www.kyivpost.com/ukraine-politics/kyiv-insists-cancellation-separatists-ids-recognition-russia.html}}</ref>。

2018年10月2日，他以年齡原因辭去聯絡組代表的職務<ref>[https://www.unian.info/politics/10279581-ukraine-s-envoy-to-minsk-talks-kuchma-going-to-quit.html Ukraine's envoy to Minsk talks Kuchma going to quit] {{Wayback|url=https://www.unian.info/politics/10279581-ukraine-s-envoy-to-minsk-talks-kuchma-going-to-quit.html |date=20210425071137 }}, [[UNIAN|UNIAN]] (29 September 2018)<br />[https://www.unian.info/politics/10283586-kuchma-concludes-work-as-ukraine-s-envoy-to-minsk-talks.html Kuchma concludes work as Ukraine's envoy to Minsk talks] {{Wayback|url=https://www.unian.info/politics/10283586-kuchma-concludes-work-as-ukraine-s-envoy-to-minsk-talks.html |date=20210428021544 }}, [[UNIAN|UNIAN]] (2 October 2018)</ref>，但在2019年6月，應[[弗拉基米尔·泽连斯基|弗拉基米尔·泽连斯基]]的邀請再度擔任該職<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/m/politics/10581132-zelensky-s-adviser-pinchuk-helps-to-persuade-kuchma-to-re-join-minsk-talks.html|title = Zelensky's adviser: Pinchuk helps to persuade Kuchma to re-join Minsk talks}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.interfax.com.ua/news/general/660169.html|title=Reznikov becomes first deputy head of Ukraine's delegation to TCG on Donbas|access-date=2022-05-02|archive-date=2021-12-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211215162151/https://en.interfax.com.ua/news/general/660169.html}}</ref>。2020年7月，他以疲倦為由再度辭職，由[[列昂尼德·克拉夫丘克|列昂尼德·克拉夫丘克]]繼任.<ref name="Service 2020">{{cite web | last=Service | first=s Ukrainian | title=Kuchma Quits As Presidential Envoy In Group For Resolving Conflict In Ukraine | website=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty | date=2020-07-28 | url=https://www.rferl.org/a/kuchma-leaves-presidential-envoy-in-group-for-resolving-conflict-in-donbas/30753521.html | access-date=2020-11-16 | archive-date=2021-08-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210827130508/https://www.rferl.org/a/kuchma-leaves-presidential-envoy-in-group-for-resolving-conflict-in-donbas/30753521.html }}</ref><ref name="Jamestown 2020">{{cite web | title=Zelenskyy Appoints Gerontocrats to Negotiate With Russia in Minsk (Part One) | website=Jamestown | date=2020-08-11 | url=https://jamestown.org/program/zelenskyy-appoints-gerontocrats-to-negotiate-with-russia-in-minsk-part-one/ | access-date=2020-11-16 | archive-date=2021-06-15 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210615172404/https://jamestown.org/program/zelenskyy-appoints-gerontocrats-to-negotiate-with-russia-in-minsk-part-one/ }}</ref>。

[[2022年俄羅斯入侵烏克蘭|2022年俄羅斯入侵烏克蘭]]期間，他表示自己不會離開烏克蘭，將與大家一起捍衛這片土地<ref>{{Cite news|title = "Damn you all!" – Kuchma on Russian invasion of Ukraine – UKRINFORM|work = UKRINFORM|date = 10 March 2022|url = https://www.ukrinform.net/rubric-polytics/3425934-damn-you-all-kuchma-on-russian-invasion-of-ukraine.html|access-date = 2022-03-11|language = en-GB|archive-date = 2022-03-13|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220313054105/https://www.ukrinform.net/rubric-polytics/3425934-damn-you-all-kuchma-on-russian-invasion-of-ukraine.html}}</ref>。

== 家族 ==
库奇马女婿[[维克托·平丘克|维克托·平丘克]]是该国第二大富豪，[[犹太人|犹太人]]，身家32亿美元。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.forbeschina.com/review/201403/0031533.shtml |title=福布斯：维克托•平丘克：乌克兰危机中的寡头 |access-date=2014-03-06 |archive-date=2022-04-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220407184658/http://www.forbeschina.com/review/201403/0031533.shtml }}</ref>

